########################### key notes#######################
1. For binary search to find mid, always use "left + (right-left)/2" to avoid overflow
why? because of the large number. Consider the left and right are both large numbers, it will add up into a even larger number.
While right-left make it more reasonable
OR use "left + right >> 1"

2. If you shouldn't use multiplication or division then think of bit operations (<<, >>)

3.